# KPF Design System Rules (Figma MCP)

Source of visual truth for the Figma library: **Option 3 / Main** (`Homepage / Desktop â€” Option 3`, node `121:62` in file `Iz5XryrkvcSuW2wIIOFM0I`).
Source of production CSS tokens: `wordpress/plugins/kpf-core/assets/stylesheet/foundation.css` (mirrored in `frontend/src/styles/components.css`).

When Figma Option 3 and CSS diverge, prefer Option 3 for new Figma work and note a code sync follow-up.

## 1. Token Definitions

### Where tokens live
- **CSS (runtime):** `:root` custom properties in `wordpress/plugins/kpf-core/assets/stylesheet/foundation.css`
- **Frontend mirror:** `frontend/src/styles/components.css` (keep in sync with foundation)
- **Figma:** Variable collections `KPF / Primitives`, `KPF / Color`, `KPF / Spacing` on the Design System page
- **No Style Dictionary / Tokens Studio pipeline yet** â€” CSS is hand-authored

### Format
```css
--kpf-parchment: #f8f4ec;   /* code Documentary Ember */
--kpf-ember: #8b1515;
--kpf-brass: #c88758;
```

Figma Option 3 Main anchors (library primitives):
- Parchment `#f4efea` Â· Ink `#12090a` Â· Ember `#bb0d0d` Â· Brass `#c9a15b` Â· Deep `#640f0e` Â· Mute `#6b5c5c`

### Naming translation
| CSS | Figma variable | WEB code syntax |
|-----|----------------|-----------------|
| `--kpf-ember` | `ember/500` (primitive) | `var(--kpf-ember)` |
| semantic bg | `color/bg/page` | `var(--kpf-parchment)` |
| semantic text | `color/text/primary` | `var(--kpf-ink)` |

Three-layer model: **Primitive â†’ Semantic â†’ Component** (never hardcode hex in components).

### Accessibility
- Body text â‰Ą 4.5:1 on parchment/surface
- Large text / UI chrome â‰Ą 3:1
- Brass decorative (`brass/500`) fails on parchment for body text â€” use `color/text/link` / `brass/700+` for text links
- Focus ring: brass soft outline (`--kpf-focus-ring`)

## 2. Component Library

### Code
- Global foundation classes: `.kpf-btn`, `.kpf-btn--primary|secondary|brass|ghost`, `.kpf-input`, `.kpf-field*`, `.kpf-link`
- React: Faust/Next pages under `frontend/src/`; forms via `FormRenderer.js`; page designs via `PageDesignRenderer.js`
- No Storybook â€” WordPress admin + foundation stylesheet are the living specs

### Figma
- Page: **Design System**
- Components use variant axes `Style` / `State` / `Icon` (leading|trailing|none) â€” not one variant per icon
- Icons: Lucide library INSTANCE_SWAP (matches `frontend/src/components/Icon.js`)

### Class â†” Figma mapping
| Figma component | CSS |
|-----------------|-----|
| Button / Primary | `.kpf-btn.kpf-btn--primary` |
| Button / Secondary | `.kpf-btn.kpf-btn--secondary` |
| Button / Outline | `.kpf-btn.kpf-btn--secondary` (outline) |
| Text Link | `.kpf-link` / `.kpf-btn--ghost` |
| Text Field | `.kpf-field` + `.kpf-input` |
| Card / Accordion | design-system only until coded |

